## Supabase Schema (canonical: `apps/client-template/supabase/client-template-schema.sql`)

Tables:
- `admin_users` ‚Äî email + role; RLS: authenticated can read own row
- `brand_settings` ‚Äî one row per `site_key`; stores site name, URL, colors, fonts, blog image prompts, CTA copy
- `blog_categories` ‚Äî per `site_id`; name, slug, sort_order, is_active
- `blog_posts` ‚Äî title, slug, content (JSON `BlogSection[]` string), status, hero_image_url, featured, approved_for_publish, scheduled_publish_at, SEO fields, author fields
- `blog_queue` ‚Äî AI generation queue (`primary_keyword`, `blog_title`, `url_slug`, `writing_guidelines`, `scheduled_publish_at`, `model_id`, `status`, `generated_post_id`) ‚öÝÔ∏è schema SQL still has older shape
- `blog_knowledge_base` ‚Äî knowledge base entries for blog writer context
- `internal_links` ‚Äî keyword ‚Üí href mappings (`keyword`, `href`, `priority`, `active`) ‚öÝÔ∏è schema SQL still has older shape
- `tracked_pages` ‚Äî `route_path`, `page_title`, `seo_title`, `meta_description`, `primary_keyword`, `is_active`, `display_order`
- `system_settings` ‚Äî key/value JSON store (e.g. `auto_publish_enabled`)

Storage: public bucket `site-assets` (folders: `images/`, `blog-featured/`, `logos/`, `og/`)

RLS rules: anon can read `brand_settings`, `blog_categories` (active), `blog_posts` (published); admins (via `admin_users` check) manage everything else.

‚öÝÔ∏è **Known drift**: `blog_queue` and `internal_links` columns in SQL differ from what `admin-core` TypeScript and Edge Functions expect. Live DBs (especially `sweet-media`) are ahead of the checked-in SQL. Always treat the TS types as source of truth.

