## Deployment (Vercel + GitHub)

**Pattern**: One GitHub repo (this monorepo), one Vercel project per client.

**Vercel project settings per client**:
- **Root Directory**: `apps/<slug>` (e.g. `apps/cipher-billing`)
- **Framework**: Next.js
- **Install**: pnpm install (at repo root)
- **Build**: `pnpm --filter @sweetmedia/<slug> build` (or turbo filter equivalent)

**Required environment variables per Vercel project**:
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` ‚Äî `https://<ref>.supabase.co`
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` ‚Äî anon/public key
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` ‚Äî same anon key (both set)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_ID` ‚Äî slug (e.g. `cipher-billing`)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` ‚Äî canonical URL (e.g. `https://cipherbilling.com`)
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` ‚Äî for postbuild sync and admin API routes
- `RESEND_API_KEY` ‚Äî contact form email delivery
- `CONTACT_TO_EMAIL`, `CONTACT_FROM_EMAIL`, `CONTACT_BRAND_NAME` ‚Äî contact route inbox + sender + label (Resend sender domain must be verified)
- `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` ‚Äî admin AI routes (`/api/admin/rewrite-blog-post`, `/api/admin/generate-seo-meta`, `/api/admin/sweet-seo/analyze`); shared from repo-root `.env`
- `SEMRUSH_API_KEY` ‚Äî Semrush keyword research routes (`/api/admin/semrush/overview`, `/api/admin/semrush/suggestions`) and `/admin/keyword-research` view; shared from repo-root `.env`
- `DATAFORSEO_LOGIN` + `DATAFORSEO_PASSWORD` ‚Äî Content Editor SERP fetch (top-20 organic + People Also Ask); shared from repo-root `.env`
- `FIRECRAWL_API_KEY` ‚Äî Content Editor competitor page scraping (JS-rendered ‚Üí clean markdown); shared from repo-root `.env`
- `GOOGLE_NLP_API_KEY` ‚Äî Content Editor entity extraction (Google Cloud Natural Language API, `analyzeEntities`); shared from repo-root `.env`
- Optional: `TRACKED_PAGE_METADATA_CACHE_SECONDS`

**Scaffold auto-writes** `.env.local` with the public Supabase vars and the contact form vars when `setup-new-client.mjs` runs successfully. `scripts/publish-client-to-vercel.mjs` then upserts those values plus shared root secrets (`OPENROUTER_API_KEY`, `SEMRUSH_API_KEY`) onto the Vercel project. Use `--project <vercel-project-name>` for brands whose Vercel project name does not match their slug (`sweet-media` ‚Üí `sweet-media-platform`, `inner-peak-colorado` ‚Üí `inner-peak-colorado-platform`).

